    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.30-31_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">30</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE ACADEMY OF AMERICAN POETS
                        <lb/>
                    1030 FIFTH AVENUE
                        <lb/>
                    NEW YORK</hi> 28
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>August 15, 1958</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Professor John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Skyrim Farm</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route No. 6</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Professor Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>The results of the balloting for the current fellowship are as follows:
                    <lb/>
                    <list>
                        <item>Robinson Jeffers      4 votes</item>
                        <item>Louise Bogan          2 votes</item>
                        <item>John Holmes           2 votes</item>
                        <item>John Crowe Ransom     2 votes</item>
                        <item>Richard Wilbur        2 votes</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                
                <p>The By-Laws provide: "In the event no one shall receive a majority vote, there shall be a second election, similarly conducted, between the two nominees who receive the highest number of votes, tie votes being counted as one."</p>
                
                <p>We ask you to vote once again for one of the previously listed names and there can obviously be no award until someone receives a majority.</p>
                
                <p>It will be remembered that we are hoping to make this award as early as possible during 1958 and to have two fellowships in 1959 in celebration of The Academy's Twenty-fifth Anniversary.</p>
                
                <p>It will be greatly appreciated if you will kindly send in your ballot at your earliest possible convenience.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very truly yours, <add>and thank you so much for all your trouble from</add></salute>
                    
                    <signed>
                        Secretary
                        Hugh Bullock
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="authorial">enclosures</note>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.30-31_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">31</fw>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE ACADEMY OF AMERICAN POETS
                        <lb/>
                    1030 FIFTH AVENUE
                        <lb/>
                    NEW YORK</hi> 28
                </ab>
                
                <note type="recipient">
                    Voted
                    8-18-58
                </note>
                
